Basic Navigation and File Management 

1. Create a folder called practice1:  	mkdir practice1
2. Enter the folder: 			              cd practice1
3. Create a text file named notes.txt : touch notes.txt
4. Add some text inside notes.txt :     echo "This is my first Linux practice file." > notes.txt
5. Display the contents of the file:    cat notes.txt
6.Append a new line to the file :      	echo "I am learning Ubuntu basics." >> notes.txt
7.Create a subfolder inside practice1: 	mkdir backup
8. Copy notes.txt to the backup folder:	cp notes.txt backup/
9.  Rename the original notes.txt to notes_old.txt       mv notes.txt notes_old.txt
10. Delete the renamed file: 		        rm notes_old.txt
11. Go back to your home directory   	  cd ~

12. Verification
ls practice1 → Deberías ver solo la carpeta backup
ls practice1/backup → Deberías ver el archivo notes.txt


